I refuse to acknowledge autism subgroups. We can't be categorised so simply, and doing so can only lead to people being denied whatever help they need if they don't fit neatly into a subgroup.

My diagnosis says autism. That's it. That's the only thing I recognise.

If you are claiming Carer's Allowance you must be working less than 18 hours a week yourself. You're only getting it if you are genuinely spending 35 hours or more caring for the disabled person. 

Plus you can only claim for one person, even if you care for multiple people. 4/x

tweet: Claiming Carer's Allowance can affect that person's benefits. It can mean they lose the Severe Disability Premium, Council Tax reduction and disability element of Pension Credit. So nobody is claiming Carer's Allowance willy-nilly. 3/x

name: Davie The Non Binary Viking ğŸ—¡ï¸
description: The Last Unicorn. Language student #ActuallyAutistic non binary/masc ğŸ³ï¸â€âš§ï¸ he/they T-started 20/10/20. Queer Polyam
tweet:
It's sad. And it looks like, for now at least, that it's going to get much worse before it starts to get better. We are going to be forced out of a lot of spaces. 

Kinda makes me glad I'm such a hermit, I feel for those who love their outside communities. They will lose a lot.

name: Davie The Non Binary Viking ğŸ—¡ï¸
description: The Last Unicorn. Language student #ActuallyAutistic non binary/masc ğŸ³ï¸â€âš§ï¸ he/they T-started 20/10/20. Queer Polyam
tweet: We shouldn't have to care how other people think and feel about us existing and living. But all I see is that people do care, and they care a lot. Not in a good way either. They police our very existence, and look for more ways to keep doing so even when the evidence is gone.

name: Davie The Non Binary Viking ğŸ—¡ï¸
description: The Last Unicorn. Language student #ActuallyAutistic non binary/masc ğŸ³ï¸â€âš§ï¸ he/they T-started 20/10/20. Queer Polyam
tweet:
And it makes me so sad. 

It feels like we can't do anything right. Some of us are desperate to assimilate, and get criticised for "upholding old fashioned stereotypes". Some of us want to live freely and authentically, and we are "freaks".

name: Davie The Non Binary Viking ğŸ—¡ï¸
description: The Last Unicorn. Language student #ActuallyAutistic non binary/masc ğŸ³ï¸â€âš§ï¸ he/they T-started 20/10/20. Queer Polyam
tweet:

There will always be something.
